# Without this, `COPY packages ./packages` / `COPY apps/* ./apps/*` in the Dockerfiles pull the
# host's locally pnpm-installed node_modules (with real files, not the container's symlinked pnpm
# store) into the build context and silently clobber the image's own `pnpm install` output —
# breaks module resolution (e.g. `prisma generate` failing with MODULE_NOT_FOUND).
#
# IMPORTANT: unlike .gitignore, a bare `node_modules/` here only matches a TOP-LEVEL match —
# it does NOT recurse into nested paths like packages/*/node_modules. Every pattern below needs
# the `**/` prefix to actually exclude nested directories throughout the monorepo.
**/node_modules/
**/.pnpm-store/

# build outputs
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.next/
**/out/
**/coverage/
**/playwright-report/
**/test-results/

# turbo
**/.turbo/

# env
.env*
!.env.example

# prisma
packages/database/generated/

# logs
**/*.log

# os
**/.DS_Store

# editor
.vscode/
.idea/

# misc
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.eslintcache
.git/
backups/
